Key Match Events: Paolo Banchero scored a team-high 34 points in his return from injury
Giannis Antetokounmpo had a game-high 41 points
Post-Match Reflections: Coach Jamahl Mosley acknowledged that there would be a transition period as they reintegrate Paolo Banchero into their attack
Others: The Orlando Magic lost to the Milwaukee Bucks 109-106
Cole Anthony, Tristan Da Silva, and Anthony Black also contributed to the Magic's offense
The defeat was the second straight for the Magic
The Magic play the Philadelphia 76ers next
